name: Teresa Kelley
description: Specialties: Buyer's Agent, Listing Agent, Short-Sale, Consulting

For as long as I can remember I wanted to be a Realtor and through my life I have been pulled into this line of work.  When I was young my mother and I didn't have much extra money to go do things so we went to a lot of open houses. I loved imagining living in them and what room would be mine but I knew we wouldn't be able to afford them.  That didn't matter to me I just loved going through them. Even to this day my mom and I still love driving around looking at homes.

Patrick and I had our first child at a young age.  My dreams of being a successful Realtor were put on hold for a while.  Now we have 5 wonderful children and I understand the many blessings as well as the hardships that come along with motherhood.  My faith in Realtors was initially strained while looking for our first home, a far from perfect fixer-upper. It was difficult finding a Realtor to help us look for that specific home so I ended up finding it myself.

Shortly before moving in to our second home I finally decided to get my license.  It was after a series of disappointments working with 5 different Realtors while trying to purchase it.  Although many of my troubles were avoidable I learned the hard way what it takes to represent your clients and how even a few oversights or simply dragging your feet can cost the clients a tremendous amount.  I decided that I could easily do what these Realtors chose not to do and made a commitment to myself to always treat my clients the way they deserve to be treated and to be an example of what a true Realtor should be.
I have built and plan to build many more long lasting friendships through my business and to help people buy and sell homes!

name: Chapin Sellin-Kurtz
description: I am an Omaha native. I grew up in Dundee and I have always loved old homes and tree lined streets. I attended Creighton University and graduated with a BSBA in Marketing in 2006.

My real estate career started in property management. I worked for a national real estate investment trust (REIT). I enjoyed working in the real estate industry and received my sales licence in 2010. I learned quickly that just like every home, every real estate transaction is different. I understand that this industry requires staying current in market trends, good communication and above all else honesty. I pride myself on protecting my clients interests with integrity and honesty.

Real estate is not my only passion the last few years. Since receiving my license I have married my best friend and we have two young daughters. I have been blessed to be able to stay home with my girls while maintaining my real estate career. Often times it is a juggle but I am happy to do what I love and be able to spend this time with my girls.
When I am not selling real estate or chasing children, my husband and I love to travel. I also enjoy spending time with my family, entertaining friends and being active.

What can you expect when working with me? I am not an agent who sells the most volume in the company but I do answer my phone (almost) everytime you call. Sometimes I have cute pint sized assistants that tag along. My clients work directly with me and we walk through the process of buying or selling a home together. A home is the biggest investment most of us will ever make. I hope that when it is time for you to make your dream come true you will allow me to help you see it through.

name: Colleen Kavan
description: With over 25 years of professional experience in home buying, Colleen Kavan is Omaha’s “Go to” agent because of her many skills related to the housing industry. For the last 10 years, Colleen has focused specifically on buying and selling homes for her clients, but what makes her most effective is the value added service she provides with vast experience in new home construction, interior design, remodeling, staging, and furniture buying. Rely on her degree in interior design to provide the hottest trends in fashion, fixtures, and décor.

Colleen is exceptionally well respected in Omaha because of her many talents and for being the multifaceted agent who vigorously protects her clients’ interests. It is through her uncompromising determination, high ethical standards, and her ability to understand the ever-changing real estate market that she has established a growing base of loyal and repeat customers, as well as countless referrals.

In buying or selling, no two needs are quite alike and Colleen is extraordinarily adept at working with her clients to find the right price range, the right conditions, and at the right time to achieve peak value. Colleen’s keen awareness of the market is only surpassed by her unwavering attention to her clients’ needs.

An Omaha native, Colleen raised her sons to believe in honesty, integrity, and always doing the right thing-principles she has carried with her into her life in real estate. She stays active in the Omaha community and dedicates her time to her family, friends, and those in need.
In everything she does, Colleen believes in challenging the status quo and she believes in making every interaction with her positive. When you choose Colleen, you choose family.

name: Julie Lauritsen
description: Julie began her career in real estate working in mortgage finance.  That experience allowed her to gain an understanding of the financial end of real estate transactions and has proven to be a valuable asset to her clients.

She has applied her expertise and market knowledge to residential and investment real estate including multi-family properties and new construction.  She is a true advocate for the real estate industry and believes that there has never been a better time to invest in real estate.  Whether it’s the home you live in or an investment purchased for cash flow or wealth building for retirement there is not a better investment opportunity.  She has demonstrated that belief by purchasing her own investment properties including a multi-family complex.

Her exceptionally loyal clientele, personal referrals and repeat business form the foundation of Julie’s career.  Putting clients goals ahead of personal gain has been the hallmark of her business and has served both she and her clients well. She has been honored as the Top Producing Individual Agent in the most productive Berkshire Hathaway Home Services office in North America 2016, 2017 and was awarded the 2018 Summit Award for Highest Per Agent Productivity for Individuals.
Julie is an enthusiastic member of the community and enjoys travel, golf, live performances, her family and showing her clientele the best that the Omaha area has to offer.

name: Cindy  Robarge
description: Real Estate continues to be an ever changing business. Working closely with my clients and helping them through the buying and selling process is my #1 goal. Every transaction is as unique as the people involved. The source of business of which I am most proud is referrals. I also enjoy hearing from my clients after the transaction is complete whether it is providing assistance with the name of a plumber, electrician, hair dresser, news of a family member of the family....

name: Lisa Harris
description: As your agent,

I bring integrity, energy, hard work and creative service in every detail of your real estate transaction. Bringing business and interior design expertise together, I offer a personalized, full-service experience with a high degree of professionalism. I have a true passion for exceeding your expections from the moment you and I begin working together.

Adventure and travel are my lifelong passions. My passport is full from living in Asia and I have just one continent left to leave my footsteps on. From trekking in Nepal to diving in Belize, I seize every opportunity to immerse myself in an adventure and a new culture. While traveling, I like to refine my culinary skills as I pick up new favorites along the way!

I realize that buying a property is the most important purchase you can make. It's not just an investment - it is your home. My attention to detail and protectiveness of your best interests ensures you'll get the home you want, with the best terms and for the lowest price.

When selling your home, I go above and beyond. I will help you prepare your home with incredible precision and assist you with decor - all with an eye for what appeals to today's buyers. Your home will be expertly priced and marketed to attract the most qualified buyer so your home sells fast.
I am ready to go to work for you today!

name: Joel Johnson
description: One of the biggest decisions a person will make is buying a home. While it is certainly an exciting time, this process can also be a time of stress. My passion is helping clients maximize the joy and excitement of home ownership and to mitigate those items that might create stress during this process.

If you are selling your home, allow me to provide and explain facts and numbers to help you price your home correctly and attract prospective buyers. Work with me to present your home in “its” best light. My goal is to create as many showings of your home as quickly as I can. As part of this process, I will call you to schedule each showing to ensure it works with your schedule. Post showing, I will contact the showing agent as soon as possible for feedback about the showing. This way, we get the feedback from the agent that is showing houses in your home’s price range and also get the feedback of their buyer on how your home compares. I will provide straightforward, open and timely communication tailored around your expectations, with a weekly summary and updates on showings and the feedback we have received. We will discuss and plan future open houses and other decisions regarding your home weekly.

At The Metro Pros, our team works together to determine correct pricing, staging suggestions, and of course marketing strategies, so that hundreds more potential buyers in our area will see your home.

I place a high value on every single relationship I make with all my clients, other agents, lenders and everyone I have the privilege of working with. I would be honored to represent you in your home buying or selling process, with the professionalism and value you expect and deserve.

Chelsea is a mother and a long distance runner.  You can often find her at local running events, or being a dedicated dance mom during competition dance season.

Real Estate is a relationship based business, and Chelsea strives to create relationships based on trust and confidence.  Getting to know people and helping them find their perfect home is her my passion.
Chelsea’s ultimate goal: a business built entirely upon referrals from clients who are completely satisfied with the professional and caring service they received.

name: Tonya Moore
description: I am a firm believer that everyone deserves to buy a home and it is my job to do everything in my power to get you there. I don’t care how low your budget is or how difficult it is to find something that suits your needs. I am not pushy. I will never sell you a home I wouldn’t consider living in myself. If it’s your best option to rent, then I will tell you that. I will NEVER jeopardize my name for a sale! I will be here for you every step along the way. Most of my career I have worked in sales and service organizations with a strong emphasis on customer satisfaction. I am also a graduate at the University of Nebraska at Lincoln and a true Husker! I pride myself on giving all my clients the most precise and up-to-date feedback on the state of the market, it’s trends, and comparable sales and property values. I provide a realistic outlook on what to expect to achieve in today’s market. My goal is to provide my clients with knowledge and strive to be very precise when it comes to pricing strategies and will always negotiate the best deal for my clients. description: Having obtained a real estate license in 1978, you can be assured you are working with someone with experience. I understand the customers' needs in a dynamic and rapidly changing real estate environment and have experience throughout the metro and surrounding communities.

Specialties, Designations & Memberships

As a member of the Omaha Board of Realtors and the National Association of Realtors, I’m kept abreast of the changes in our real estate market. In addition to residential real estate, I have over ten years of experience in new construction.

I enjoy working with first time home buyers to help them with their first home purchase.  It is my goal to educate and inform.  Whether this is your first home or you are an experienced buyer or seller, it is my goal to ensure you are making a well-informed decision.

As a local resident, I know the area and can give you access to information that you can never find on the Internet! Married with 2 grown children and two grand-daughters, I am a professional whom you can count on for all your home buying or selling needs.
Give me a call, or send me an email and let me put my expertise and company to work for you today!  Customer services… Who you work with matters!

name: Nicole Mattson
description: Nicole Mattson is an Omaha based agent who began her real estate career in 2020. She brings time-tested sales acumen and a genuine desire to help to all clients buy and sell residential properties.   Nicole is driven, self-motivated, and knows hard work gets results. Without any encouragement from family, she made the decision to seek higher education and was awarded an academic scholarship to Creighton University, having become the first in her family to graduate from college. Her career in business led to her to roles in sales, where she successfully gained market share for Fortune 500 companies. She’ll put her many years as a sales professional to work for you.  She will focus on your needs and treat you like a valued friend throughout the buying and selling process.  Nicole welcomes first time home buyers, veterans, and those interested in investment properties.

With over 20 years of experience in Real Estate sales, training and management, I offer a tremendous service. I can help you with all your Real Estate needs including buying, selling, short sales, loan modifications, investments, foreclosures, new construction, villa communities, condominium developement, relocation, commercial, HUD sales and tax exchanges just to name a few. I am the 2019 Omaha Area Board of Realtors President. I am currently an intructor at REEsults Coaching for those of you who are interested in getting into this wonderful business. In addition, I was the President of the Chamber of Commerce so, helping buiness owners is in my blood. Here at Berkshire Hathaway AMB HS we are raising the bar on Business Brokerage.  Ethics, confidentiality and transperancy are what we believe makes for a successful transfer or purchase of a business.   I'd welcome the opportunity to give you a valuation on your business and help you prepare it to sell.  Please contact me if you are considering a sale of your business or the purchase of one.

name: Kara Bellino
description: With her genuine nature, eye for design and love for Omaha – Kara Bellino strives to exceed expectations with each and every client. A true people person, her upbeat spirit is truly contagious.

What makes Kara standout from the rest. Not only does she have experience as a buyer & sellers agent. When she is not selling real estate you can find her working alongside her husband flipping homes & searching for properties to add to their rental portfolio.

“…What I adore most is getting to know you. Everyone has their unique story. The fun part about my job is, I get to learn that story! It is such a rewarding feeling contributing to someone else’s happiness and helping them find a place to call home.”

name: Gayla Leathers
description: Gayla specializes in offering excellent customer service to her clients. She strives for excellence always going the extra mile. Whether buying or selling a home, Gayla and her hand-picked team of outstanding agents and support staff are always on a mission of exceeding their clients’ expectations.

Gayla has a fondness working with empty nesters and guiding them through the process of downsizing. She has earned the nationally recognized Seniors Real Estate Specialist® designation. She also has a profound amount of respect for Veterans and the Military and is certified as a Military Relocation Professional.

Outside of work her life revolves around her husband, Ted, and their eight ridiculously adorable grandchildren. She loves home improvement projects, family vacations, and soaking up as much time as possible with her grandkids.

name: Tayler VanPelt
description: Hi! I am here to help you in
anyway
I can! If you are a first time home buyer, or if you are ready to sell your house and buy your dream home GIVE ME A CALL!  :)
I don't sell houses I help you find your future!

name: Renae VerMaas
description: Renae VerMaas, a Realtor with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, and part of the All Metro Real Estate Group, is an Omaha native who has always had an interest in real estate.  Her interest started as a young child, as her family often moved every couple of years. She loved looking at houses and learning the real estate language as a young child, even asking her parents at the age of 8, if they could write a contingency offer on a house. Her interest also came from her mother who spent time as a Realtor and several years in the mortgage business.

Prior to following her dream to become a realtor, Renae spent 20 plus years working in non-profit and youth programs.  Renae prides herself in delivering outstanding customer service, honesty, integrity, and client relationships that far exceed the sale of a home.  Renae believes that not only is your home an investment, but as the saying goes, “There’s No Place Like Home”.  Renae’s goal is to make her clients her number one priority, and help them find that perfect house to call home.

Outside of real estate, Renae loves to travel, attend her children’s sporting and dance events, and simply loves being at home entertaining family and friends.  Renae has been married to her husband Scott for 23 years. They have three children, Nathan (19) a freshmen and baseball player at North Dakota State University, Bailey (16) a sophomore at Millard North High School, and an avid competitive dancer, & Caden (14) an 8th grader at Kiewit Middle School who plays competitive baseball and football.  Renae has also been a part of the TeamMates Mentoring Program as a mentor for the past 5 years.

name: Barb Bettin
description: When selling or buying real estate, it's all about the timing....

As a Realtor, my job is to listen to your story and then ask questions. Whether you are considering a purchase for the first or third time, it's all about what works for you at the time you need it to work. I let my clients set the pace and I adapt my focus on what my they tell me is important.

I grew up in the Omaha area and have enjoyed my real estate career for the past 20+ years helping buyers and sellers whether purchasing new construction, downsizing or relocating out of town as an advocate for their move before, during and after the closing of their home.

I am married to my high school sweetheart and together we have 5 children, 8 grandchildren. We enjoy spending time camping, boating or riding our Harley motorcycle on the weekends with family and friends.

name: Dallas Zimmer
description: Prior to joining Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I spent over 18 years in the corporate environment.  As a former operations manager and management & leadership development leader, I am a detail oriented and results driven professional who strives to meet your every need.  I hold licenses in both Iowa and Nebraska; as well as the Military Relocation Professional (MRP) designation from the National Association of Realtors.  This is the only one of its kind in the industry.  As someone who has relocated multiple times myself, with kids, I understand first hand the stresses involved with these moves - both as a buyer and a seller.  I will use these experiences to your advantage!  So why choose me?
Buyers:

Understanding your needs prior to the search will streamline the process and maximize the one thing you can never get back - time!  Our goal is to bring you only the homes that actually meet your needs.  We have an extensive network that allows us to find you the perfect home, sometimes even before it comes on the market.  I am excited to help you achieve your real estate goals.
Sellers:

With the vast majority of home searches beginning online, ensuring your photos make your home appealing to buyers is critical.  Our trusted partners assist us in bringing out the best in your home.  Our team is active in the social media networks, connecting your home with as many potential buyers as possible.  We actively market our properties to our network of buyers and agents as well as being connected with relocation companies for those out of town buyers.
Thank you!
Dallas

The Larsen Group (Steve Larsen and Jim Braun) proudly represent Trademark Homes. Both Steve and Jim are experienced agents and are familar with the home building and buying process.

Tammy began her real estate career as a sales agent in 2000 and obtained her brokers license in 2007. She owned her own boutique real estate brokerage for 5 years before joining Omaha market leader, Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices | Ambassador Real Estate.

Tammy is a Certified Residential Specialist(CRS) an achievement that only 4% of all REALTORS ® worldwide have attained. Additionally, Tammy is ranked in the top 3% of all agents in the BHHS worldwide network. Through the years hundreds of busy professionals & busy families alike have appreciated Tammy’s passionate and personable approach to doing business. Known for her astute negotiation skills, she takes great pride in protecting her clients best interests, whether that be in contract negotiations or by advocating for homeownership & private property rights by meeting with legislators at the state level and on Capitol Hill in Washington DC.

Tammy is a dedicated Mother to three grown children. They are her greatest joy & accomplishment. In her free time she can be found traveling the world, sharing dinner, wine, & great conversation with friends; attending her niece’s activities; gourmet cooking; reading & researching; or working on her own “honey-do list” around her historic home.

name: Desiree Troia

With her specialized computer technology and administrative skills, Desiree coordinates every detail of Team Leathers’ real estate listings and closings. Her primary focus is making sure her client’s individual needs are a top priority. Desiree is an outstanding, hard-working real estate agent for the Team Leathers’ family of exceptional Omaha-metro licensed realtors.

description: Growing up in Nebraska, I have lived in the Omaha area for more than 25 years - raising a family of 3 girls in the Omaha/Elkhorn area.  Being around this long, I am very familiar with the city and all that it has to offer.  This knowledge is invaluable when showing your home to perspective buyers and when helping buyers find the perfect home and location in the city.  I am a proud real estate professional that is focused on going above and beyond for my clients.  I bring over 25 years of top notch client service to the table. When not selling homes you will find me playing with my rescue dogs and spending time with family - preferably on a beach somewhere!

name: Tanya Blocker
description: I have lived in the Omaha Metropolitan Area since 1997 and know the local real estate market better than some residents who have lived here their entire lives! Known by my clients and colleagues as an "intentional listener", I feel I have a gift for understanding what is important to my clients and then executing a plan of action that will help them achieve their goals.

name: Jill Marie Bartling
description: Starting in the Real Estate business in 2002, I have the confidence, knowledge and expertise to help you with any of your Residential Real Estate needs & love helping every family find a home that perfectly fits their needs, whether it's buying an existing home or building a brand new one.  Born and raised in South Omaha, Nebraska, I spent the weekends as a kid in the backseat of our family car with my two older Brothers, as my My Dad & Mom took us on Sunday drives.  Little did I know, I was learning how to take every back road and alley in town and by the time I was 16 (ok 15), I was driving through out Omaha knowing exactly where I was going and how to take a detour to get there faster if I needed to.

What I love about Omaha, is we're your little, big town!  Omaha, Nebraska maintains that “small town” feeling, with some big city amenities.  Enjoy the World Famous, Omaha Henry Doorly Zoo, catch a College World Series Baseball game at TD Ameritrade Park in June, People watch in the Old Market while attending the Summer Arts Festival and Farmers Markets, or while you are on a stroll for a date night.  Don't forget to entice your appetite with some of the best eats around, like the Ruben Sandwich created right here in Omaha.  Walk the 3000 sq. ft. floating bridge over the Missouri River from downtown Omaha to Council Bluffs, Iowa.  (yes, it's walkable, you can one foot in Nebraska & one foot in Iowa at the same time!).
My main goal for you always, is to handle the complex details, so it's an easy transition from home to home, so if you're selling, buying or building, I'm happy to help!
We Sell Homes, not Houses.

name: Mike Blackmon
description: Mike is the Commercial Division Manager for the Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate company, serving the Omaha Metro, Nebraska and Iowa.

With a background in sales, banking, and real estate, Mike is 'client-centric', - a 'matchmaker' for his clients and their real estate needs.  Includes listing and selling brokerage, landlord AND tenant rep leasing, revitalization and/or re-purposing existing buildings, and new developments.

Our Commercial Division has a very strong background and experience in all aspect of new development, construction management, project management, asset management, critical analyis of a building and/or an entire project for analyzing the project feasibility and potential profitability.

Mike currently serves as Vice-Chair of the MRCIE (Midlands Regional Commercial Information Exchange) serving Nebraska and Iowa, beginning May1, 2017.  Mike is a member of Governmental Affairs Committee for the Omaha Area Board of Realtors.

Historically, Mike has been in consultative selling all of his life.  Mike invested 12 years in the life insurance and employee benefits business, including financial planning, estate planning, and employee benefit planning, for the medium size business owners and high income earners.  Mike earned his professional designation as a CLU in 1976 from The American College in Bryn Mawr, PA, which has proved time and again to be valuable background to assist his real estate clients.

An opportunity arose to enter the banking business in a small town bank, where Mike learned all facets of banking, from the teller to the regulatory filings to agriculture, consumer, and commercial business lending.

These two careers had a huge impact and fabulous background training for a career in real estate since 1981.  Back in Omaha since 2000, Mike has increased his commercial sales, real estate investment analysis skills, and developement and asset management skills with hands-on involvement and counseling a myriad of diffferent experience level of investors and owner/users of commercial real estate.

Mike works by referral.  If you or your friends and/or associates have a project you are interested in, please feel free to contact Mike to see if we - The Project, Mike - or one of our Team, and You, are a 'Match'!!  We love to help make a project come to life and become a success.

I am a transplant from the West Coast with roots in Nebraska and have now called the Omaha area my "home" for 20 years.  I attended the University of Nebraska in Lincoln and Kearney where I studied in Information Systems and graduated top of my department.  I have combined my technical training with my real estate expertise to provide my clients with an "edge".

I belong to a family of real estate professionals.  I work on the residential side and my husband is a commercial broker. I have one uncle who owns a brokerage on the western slopes of Colorado and another who sells farms and ranches in Western Nebraska.  My Grandfather dealt with all forms of real estate across the state.  Real Estate is in my blood.

I lost my mother to cancer in 1998.  When you experience loss like this, you learn to never take advantage of the precious time God gives us. I love to fill my days fellowshipping with friends & family & colleagues, enriching my mind and body with mental and physical exercise, and finding the best deals for my buyers and the best leads for my sellers.  I volunteer my time to Road to Recovery (driving cancer patients to their treatments) and I participate in the Race for the Cure every year.
My husband and I are the lucky parents of two spirited little boys:  Sheppard is 5 years old and Sawyer is 2 years old.  These boys keep us on our toes, but we wouldn't have it any other way!

I tell you all of this above because I run a relationship-based business.  I want you to know who you will be dealing with on your home purchase or sale.  I won't sell you a property I find inadequate or feel is not a good fit for you.  I won't tell you what you want to hear just to "win" your listing.  I will tell you the truth and I will back it with factual data because we are a team and it wouldn't be a good team player if I wasn't truthful and doing my job.  I care more about your complete satisfaction than making just one sale. My ultimate goal is to make you a raving fan so that you want to do business with me again and feel compelled to refer me to your friends. I know I have to earn that privilege.
Call me for a no-obligation consultation :)

description: Before getting into real estate I worked as a Patient Advocate helping families who were on the brink of financial distress; their child was in the hospital and was under insured or uninsured. The decisions that you are about to make are not just about real estate, but what you need from the home, what your current life circumstances are and your goals for your life - among other things.  Whether you are buying your first home, needing something bigger, downsizing, buying an income property or anything inbetween, I can help you and look forward to it!

It’s this attention to detail and dedication to quality that has allowed RMR to establish itself as a premier contractor in the Midwest.

Before starting his professional career in Chicago, Robbie was an all-american baseball player at Lewis University and signed a professional contract with the Houston Astros. Robbie also holds a real estate license with his family’s real estate company, Murante Real Estate, in Omaha, NE.

name: Elizabeth Lowndes
description: At Baby Boomer Plus Real Estate Group, our mission is to provide and facilitate the home selling process for our mature clientele with professionalism and compassion.

Our goal is to assist Boomers, Seniors and Elders with moves to their next residence. Baby Boomer Plus Real Estate Group is the turnkey solution to managing all aspects of the sale of an estate. Our group of SRES (Senior Real Estate Specialists) work with clients and their families to SIMPLIFY the process. Our commitment is to make the transition as stress free and efficient as possible.

We've teamed up with local professionals to offer specialized home sale services- from downsizing, property liquidation, senior moving, and independent/assisted/memory care living...one complete start to finish service.
Our services are tailored to you and your family's unique needs throughout Omaha and the Metro Area. Call your Senior Real Estate Specialist today....
Elizabeth Lowndes 402.968.0175

name: Deb Cizek
description: Deb Cizek graduated from the University of Northern Colorado and continued on to receive her Master’s degree from the University of Nebraska  - Omaha. She taught gifted education for 11 years. After teaching, Deb got her real estate license and has been selling real estate for over 30 years.

Deb started out as an individual agent for BJ Brown and then moved to Prudential and then formed The Cizek // Stork Group. She has had her team for over 20 years. The team has ranked in the top ten 5 times in the last few years. Her team has remained in the top 1% of the nation for both number of transactions and gross commission income each year for the past 25 years. She attributes her success to her unique approach to the industry and believes investing in a business coach who pushes her to take a pro-active plan works.
Deb is very excited to form The Cizek // Stork Group with Terry Stork this year. They have been good friends and colleagues for over 30 years.

Deb feels blessed to have found a group of professionals who understand that real estate is the business and clients are the priority. The group motivates and encourages each other to consistently achieve top results. The Cizek // Stork Group is not just a real estate team but a family!
Ron and Deb Cizek enjoy their home on Bennington Lake and love spending time with their 4 sons and 12 grandchildren.

name: Ellen Jaworski
description: I am a licensed Real Estate professional with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices in Omaha, NE. I have been in Real Estate for 15 years and I couldn't be happier. I can truly say that I love waking up every morning to go to work!
While attending the University of Nebraska - Omaha, I changed my major from Interior Design to Real Estate and Land Use Economics and have never looked back.

As a lifelong resident of Omaha, I will put my local knowledge to work for you to help make your real estate transaction a great one. I make sure to keep you informed, provide you with feedback and protect your interests in a pleasant, professional, hard-working, enthusiastic, and organized manner. I will ease your fears and apprehensions by staying in constant contact with you. If a situation should arise, I will contact you and solve the problem on your behalf.

I thouroughly enjoy meeting new people and building lasting relationships that continue even after the transaction is complete. Most importantly, I listen to you, understand your needs, and I will work tirelessly on your behalf.

name: Ryan Potter
description: Ryan Potter is a passionate entrepreneur in the real estate industry who has clients constantly itching to work with him. He has become one of the most sought out real estate agents to work with in Omaha, Nebraska because of his reputation as "the social media guy," and his expertise on how to strategically invest in real estate. His personality, drive, and creativity to be different, has separated him from the competition. Ryan is also an author, professional speaker, and a real estate coach to students all over the United States. Ryan currently leads his own team at Berkshire Hathaway Home Services Ambassador Real Estate called the Potter Real Estate Group.
To schedule your free consultation with Ryan, simply email him at
ryan.potter@bhhsamb.com
and coffee or lunch will be on him.

name: Tami White
description: Tami started her real estate career in 2006 working as the administrative assistant and is co-owner with her husband for their appraisal company.
Tami obtained her Real Estate Sales License in 2016 and started her career working for a small, local agency where she has sustained a multimillion dollar producer every year.
Tami's diverse expertise allows her to assist with buyers and sellers of residential, commercial, agricultural and business properties.

name: Tabitha Cooper
description: Thank you for visiting my page! I am thrilled to help you find your new home or help you sell your existing home. Real Estate is a genuine passion of mine and being a Veteran of the United States Air Force and married to a Retired USAF
stud muffin
, we know a thing or two about BUYING AND SELLING homes :)

Having been the trainer here at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I am immensely qualified to walk through this process with you, hand in hand, answering any and all questions along the way and having fun while doing it. Buying and Selling homes can be super stressful. But, it can also be super exciting. The thrill of buying a brand new home, your first ever home, downsizing, upsizing, buying an investment property etc...this process should me memorable (in a good way). The thrill of selling a home so that you can move on to the next phase or chapter in your life, turning that equity into (cash monies), should also be a memorable process (in a good way).

click here to check out our Models

Call or text me today at 402-210-5055

name: Chad Scott
description: For the past 20 years, Chad’s entrepreneurial drive has led him to embark on various business ventures in cities such as Atlanta, Detroit, and Phoenix. But, as an Omaha native, his goal has been to provide the community with comparable opportunities and activities as those available in larger cities. Chad’s company has sponsored several community events for inner city youth, as well as networking mixers for local business owners in the area. These functions were predicated on his belief that bringing together proprietors of different backgrounds and interests was the best way for the small business community to grow and thrive. As a result of participating in these mixers, he opened a couple of retail establishments while continuing his education in marketing.

As the son of an engineer, Chad began to learn about real estate and has invested in homes requiring extensive rehabilitation. Over the past 10 years, he has familiarized himself with the difficulties that tend to arise acquiring real property. This being the case, his goal as a licensed realtor is to make the process of buying and selling your property as efficient and painless as possible.
Through hard work, tenacity, and diligence, Chad has remained in service to his community and has developed strong ties with those who consider him trustworthy, dedicated, and always willing to help.

name: Dick Gibb
description: Dick began his sales career as a buyer for women's clothing at Brandies and eventually owned his own local chain of stores called "Gibb's Girls." In 1990, he decided to
stop filling closets
and start
selling them
instead! After working a few years solo, Dick's business grew to the point that he needed someone to help him stay organized.
Sherri Tyler

joined his team as an administrative assistant. Dick first met Sherri and her family when he sold them their first home in 1993. Over the years, a few more agents joined the team to work solely as Buyer's Agents, while Dick manages the listing side of the process; meet
Jonathan Mueller
and
Rosalia Gish

. What began as a sole proprietorship is now a thriving LLC; BHO Enterprises, specializing in Residential Sales, Military Relocation and Investment Properties. People outgrow their homes, just like they do their clothing. Now, Dick and his team help refit them in a home that better meets their needs. If your home no longer meets your needs, we would be happy to assist you in finding a better fit. Please call or text us today. We look forward to helping find the perfect fit for your lifestyle.

name: Brian Wilson
description: As a real estate agent at BHHS Ambassador Real Estate, I understand the importance of working with a professional agent who will have your best interests at heart. With over 24 years of experience in real estate & 20 of those specializing in new construction, you can rely on me for great advice, whether it is guiding you seamlessly through your home building project or helping you buy or sell an existing home. I proudly represent Al Belt Custom Homes, one of the Omaha areas’s premier builders.I believe in customer service above all else – believing that every individual deserves my full commitment and loyalty. As a local resident, I know the area & can give you access to information that you will never find on the Internet! I am supported by a company that understands the customer’s needs in a dynamic and rapidly changing real estate environment. This enables me to offer the most powerful real estate services to home buyers & sellers, including relocation services, financing, title insurance & much more.
Give me a call, or send me an email and let me put my expertise to work for you today!

name: Terry Stork
description: I have over 35 years of experience in the Omaha real estate market as well as proudly representing Woodland Homes, Inc. for over 30 of those years. I am ready to bring top notch service to you whether you are buying, selling, or building your dream home.

Woodland Homes is a custom home builder committed to ensuring high quality and expert craftsmanship.  Woodland Homes builds all over the Omaha metro area and specializes in building both single family residences and villas.

Success in this industry depends on the relationships I have with my clients.  I believe in being professional, honest, and loyal.  I am here to listen to your wants and needs and to make buying, selling, or building a home as enjoyable as possible for you.
I am so grateful to be a part of such a monumental moment in your life!

name: Nick Navarrette
description: I'm an expert real estate agent with BHHS Ambassador Real Estate in Omaha, NE and the nearby area, providing home-buyers and sellers with professional, responsive and attentive real estate services. Want an agent who'll really listen to what you want in a home? Need an agent who knows how to effectively market your home so it sells? Give me a call! I'm eager to help and would love to talk to you.

name: Alex Bolduc
description: For Alex, it was a calling. Ever since he first started studying for his license in high school, Alex knew he would become a full-time real estate agent.

A lifelong Council Bluffs native, Alex has a deep understanding of the market and will work tirelessly to get your deal done as smoothly and seamlessly as possible. He understands the entire metropolitan area and is licensed in both Nebraska and Iowa.
You’ll find Alex’s energy, passion, an
d attitude for helping clients refreshing and reassuring.

name: Heather Starmer
description: I have been in the real estate industry since 2001 and I truly love what I do! In 2015 I joined the Lori Paul Group at Berkshire Hathaway Home Services Ambassador Real Estate. I obtained my real estate license in 2008 and along the way discovered that selling residential real estate is where my heart was! My ultimate goal is to provide my clients with the best possible service in order to achieve their goals and desires. I am proud to operate my business mainly from referrals. Referrals from a past client is the biggest compliment I could be given!  I have received many accolades from past and present clients about my exceptional knowledge of the real estate market and dedication to making buying or selling homes a true pleasure for my clients. I attribute my success to many years in the industry and perfecting the process for my clients which means constant communication with my clients and everyone involved in the process. I continue to stay informed in the real estate market to ensure I have the latest info regarding real estate, so I can represent my clients to the best of my ability.

I also hold a bachelor’s degree in marketing and management therefore I am knowledgeable in how to effectively promote my client’s properties in order to get them sold. I also have a management background to effectively manage the process of a real estate transaction to get to a successful close.

Lastly but certainly not least, I am a mother of 2 very busy boys and enjoys spending time with them when I am not busy in real estate! Both of my boys are very active in Cub Scouts, soccer, baseball and basketball! I love watching them in their elements!

name: Laura Schwarz
description: Welcome to our website!  Ryan and I are both full-time Realtors with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate - Combining years of industry experience, intimate knowledge of Omaha and its surrounding areas and living by the golden rule is what separates us from the competition.

We understand you have hundreds of choices when it comes to working with a Realtor and that's what drives us everyday to exceed the expectations of our clients. Please don't hesitate to contact us with any of your real estate needs or questions.

name: Kelly Kontz
job_title: Owner - The Key Group and Staged & Rearranged
description: Known for delivering personalized attention, out-of-the-box thinking and referral-worthy experiences, Kelly Kontz thrives in the luxury home market with her “client first” mentality. Her real estate business has grown to be one of the top in Omaha, just through the word of mouth from her clients! Very impressive! She is a true businesswoman who just happens to sell real estate…

“To me, success in real estate is all about the relationships I have with my clients... I consider my clients my friends & I feel truly blessed that I can be a small part of such a big decision in their lives. What a wonderful & rewarding experience handing them their Keys! I love to see them smile!”

Kelly has been setting and achieving big goals ever since graduating from Minnesota State University in Mankato with a double major in marketing & management in a record 3 1⁄2 years! Kelly is an accomplished entrepreneur who is not afraid of taking risks. Before getting into real estate over 14 years ago, Kelly started a very successful event planning business in Sioux Falls, SD, a performance dog biscuit business in Billings, MT and now along with being a Multi-Million Dollar Club Producing Realtor, Kelly owns The Key Group – A Premier Real Estate Group; Staged & Rearranged, P.C., a professional home staging company; Pride in Properties, a rental management company. Her most rewarding collaboration, though, is her family – Husband of 20 years Steve and two sons, Nick and Alex.

name: Marie Otis
description: It's more than four walls and a roof over your head. It's a place where families come together to create memories that will last for generations. Whether I am representing you in the sale of your current home or assisting you with finding your new home, it is an honor to be a small part of creating your family memories.

Before I started my Real Estate career, I was a Medical Technologist and Microbiologist at the Mayo Clinic. After moving to Omaha I went to graduate school at UNO to be a counselor. These experiences have shaped the way I approach my life and business, with thoughtful purpose and methodical organization.

In the 16 years I have been a Realtor I have worked with many different types of clients from military families, to first time buyers, to relocating families, to downsizing empty-nesters. The common traits I believe all clients are looking for is someone who will listen, take the time to understand their wants and needs in their next home and educate them on the process of buying or selling a home. I will do everything in my power to deliver the results you expect with state of the art communication, a detailed and organized plan of action, marketing, web presence and Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate technology. My commitment is to provide you with a smooth transaction by giving you exceptional service and complete satisfaction.

name: Steve VanHerpen
description: Bringing extensive knowledge of the real estate market.  I offer all my clients an unmatched level of service.  My formal education and training added with many years of purchasing, owning and selling property allows me to excel at all levels needed to finalize a real estate transaction.  Growing up in a military family, I know what it takes to move from place to place every three to four years.  I also know all the stresses moving from place to place can cause and know what it takes to eliminate those stresses.  I have lived in the Omaha, Bellevue, and Papillion areas  for over 19 years and have a vast knowledge of the area.  If you’re looking for a realtor that is willing to work endlessly to ensure your home buying and selling needs are taken care of, look no further.

name: Stephanie Vance
description: I am married, have two daughters, two dogs, and a cat. A few things I really love doing in my down time include – reading, traveling, Country dancing, photography, spending time with my family outside, and love to volunteer in my free time as well (I love going out to meet new people). I have my bachelor’s degree from University of Nebraska. I have over 10 years of customer service experience and am a native of the Omaha area that will help you in your journey to moving into your new home.
Thank you for giving me the opportunity to work with you!

description: The unique value I bring to my clients is the ability to walk into a property and advise you whether or not it's a good investment. I like to utilize my staging abilities to enhance the best qualities and features of the home. With my vendors, we can have your home painted and carpeted and on the market or move in ready, in a matter of days. I am willing to undertake the detail no matter the size, to get the job done.
SOMETHING ABOUT EVA

Eva’s strong suits are her patient and empathetic personality and keen listening skills, attributes she honed during her years as a nurse. Eva has built a reputation with her clients for her attention to detail and one-to-one communication, as she helps them navigate their way through the process. Not one to shy away from challenges, Eva has gained a reputation for taking on and completing transactions others might shy away from. Eva is a certified stager, giving her the knowledge and understanding to counsel her clients so that their home can realize its maximum potential.

name: Jeff Salem
description: Jeff Salem is a co-owner and transaction manager with the Salem Real Estate Group at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. Jeff is a retired Lt Col in the United States Air Force. description: Thomas is a lifelong native of Omaha being born in Des Monies, IA and moving here at the early age of one. “My goal is to provide the most education and leverage for my family, friends, and clients in helping them deal with one of the largest assets in life; Real Estate!”

Thomas attended Skutt Catholic High School, graduated in 2012, and has recently graduated from the University of Nebraska – Omaha with a Bachelor’s of Science in Aviation, Professional flight and a Minor in Business. The first line of work Thomas began, shortly before graduating college, was working as a Certified Flight Instructor. This position gave him the ability to educate in an effective way, as well as adapt to people of all ages and ethnicities.  He has gained a great understanding of what it takes to work with clients and keep things simple, engaging, informative and fun. He’s here for the millennial generation with the most updated applications and systems ready to make your home process a breeze!
In his spare time Thomas loves to be with the large, confusing family he has grown up with, play a good round of golf, and maintain a physically fit lifestyle to gain the most out of life.
